history.content:
Peter Abbeil and CS188 are really prestigious in the entire nation. 

However, when comparing it to other CS upper div courses,  the workload of CS188 is very easy. It also has edx version which provides all the material that you could self-study.

In terms of content, CS188 will introduce basic RL and Markov Process. These are very different from what people think of the title (It's AI, but not NN or ML or TF).

If you want to do RL research, I think the course would be helpful. However, those who do research are usually capable of self-studying the materials and take 189.

If you want to take this course to learning Neural Network or Machine learning theory or programming, you should take 189 & 294 instead, and 188 is unrelated to that. 

If you take it for fun, definitely go to it. It would be a light-workload and interesting class.
